 established design principles and covers all aspects of web design—from planning to production to maintenance. The guide also shows how these principles apply in web design projects whose primary concerns are information design, interface design, and efficient search and navigation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aWeb sitesxDesign. 7aCOMPUTERS / Web / Design.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300225259423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300225259/original  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles